description:
In 1888, a message was shared that could have changed the face of Adventism. The 1888 General Conference session was the most famous GC session in Seventh Day Adventist history, but unfortunately it is remembered for negative reasons. It was not reality accepted by everyone, and the fallout of this fractured state of the church still haunts us today. What lessons can we learn today to avoid the pitfalls of the past?

To find out more about the 1888 General Conference Session visit our website to read our extended article.
